ales extragonadales (mediastino)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"83","text":"Linfoma No-Hodgkin","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"83","text":"Próstata → riesgo MENOR que población general","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"59","text":"Autoinmune","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"AR, LES, Hashimoto, DM1","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"59","text":"Pulmonar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"EPOC y neumonía más frecuentes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"59","text":"Dentofacial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Taurodontismo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Prognatismo mandibular","guid":"RVOAOpFO9XgTGH5_Z0NqIA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"CARIOTIPO en sangre periférica\\N→ definitivo","guid":"_WZJZumZ-_n1sLhkFTvzxQ","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"Mínimo 20 células en metafase","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"FISH o citogenética tradicional","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"96","text":"Si sospecha mosaicismo → fibroblastos piel o tejido testicular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"96","text":"Diagnóstico presuntivo\\Naceptable si","guid":"aMmBq0FWu0lcTSPIpoMTAA","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"Hipogonadismo primario + fenotipo clásico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"Sin interés en fertilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"96","text":"CARIOTIPO\\NOBLIGATORIO si","guid":"wcgZ_QwoGswaLZ0SLKc0-w","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Desea fertilidad (microTESE/ICSI)","guid":"u_lVVKs6yWt4sJ_rgu0baQ","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"Confirmación definitiva","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"96","text":"Prenatal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"ADN libre materno NO es diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"Confirmar con amniocentesis/biopsia vellosidades","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Terapia con\\NTestosterona","guid":"ojTEIMkjC6mezquNffwU3Q","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Neonatos → curso\\Ncorto para micropene","guid":"u7OBMKw1TGXah9aq-OT_Xw","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"Cipionato/enantato 25 mg IM mensual x 3 dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"ÚNICA indicación prepuberal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"Prepuberales 1-12 años → CONTRAINDICADO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Riesgo cierre epifisario temprano","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"117","parent":"111","text":"Púberes 13-18 años\\N→ inicio gradual","guid":"1XXAU_j_nHXyJzXcKzNgQg","children":[{"id":"118","parent":"117","text":"50-100 mg IM mensual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"117","text":"Evitar formulaciones larga duración","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"111","text":"Adultos →\\Ndosis plena\\Nestándar","guid":"lrwT6rsQ_ETjgl933p-KMQ","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"Iniciar 1/4-1/2 dosis si T muy baja","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"TRATAR incluso si T normal con LH elevada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"111","text":"Beneficios → densidad ósea, perfil metabólico, ánimo, libido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"111","text":"Solo 41-49% pacientes adhieren a TRT (Birch 2023)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"110","text":"Manejo\\NInfertilidad","guid":"ODroYkZ8WhUMwwaq57PhkA","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"MicroTESE → tasa recuperación esperma 45-50%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"ICSI → ~50% concepción con esperma recuperado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"SUSPENDER T 3-6 meses antes de microTESE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"Permite rebote gonadotropinas endógenas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"125","text":"Criopreservación adolescente\\N→ no de rutina","guid":"KXl3sFiQuI7iBHxIcC528Q","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"Espermiograma >16 años o mosaicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"Si hay esperma → congelar","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"110","text":"Ginecomastia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Mamoplastia de reducción","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Realizar MESES DESPUÉS de iniciar T","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"110","text":"Screening\\Noncológico","guid":"bygapkyTrOV_wKm-U2GFyQ","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Examen mamario cada 1-2 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"136","text":"Mamografía SOLO si masa sospechosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"110","text":"Enfoque multidisciplinario\\N(guía SfE 2021)","guid":"YZYNdEKPQ8XOFq_GWObINg","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"Endocrinología + urología + psicología","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"Coaching estilo de vida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"Densitometría periódica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"139","text":"Fonoaudiología/educación especial si déficit cognitivo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"144","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"zoTox5Hbpc0XU8vWQH8Qtg","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"Testículos ≤4 cc + FIRMES = casi patognomónico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"144","text":"NO confiar solo en T total → buscar LH elevada como signo de compensación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"144","text":"FSH siempre > LH → patrón clásico Klinefelter","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"144","text":"Riesgo TVP/EP es del SÍNDROME → T no lo causa, podría reducirlo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"144","text":"MicroTESE funciona → 50% recuperación, NUNCA durante TRT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"144","text":"Micropene neonatal → ventana única para T corta (25mg x3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"144","text":"Ca mama 50x → examen mamario anual, pero ca próstata es MENOR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"144","text":"Talla alta con piernas largas (eunucoide) ≠ otros hipogonadismos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"144","text":"T más alta se asocia a mejor cognición → refuerza indicación TRT","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"144","text":"SUBDIAGNÓSTICO masivo → buscar activamente en hipogonadismo + infertilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"1. Matsumoto AM, et al. Klinefelter syndrome. UpToDate. 2026.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"2. Birch S. VTE in Klinefelter syndrome. Trends Urol Mens Health. 2023;14(6):23-26.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"3. Jayasena CN, et al. SfE guidelines for TRT in male hypogonadism. Clin Endocrinol. 2022;96(2):200-219.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"155","text":"4. Simonetti L, et al. Higher testosterone and cognitive functions in KS. Andrology. 2025;13(8):2216-2226.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"155","text":"5. Chang S, et al. Platelet aggregation in KS not aggravated by TRT. Andrology. 2023;11(3):456-463.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"155","text":"6. Liang B, et al. KS in transgender individuals: systematic review. Clin Endocrinol. 2022;97(1):3-12.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":161,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"s